                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5041/7: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-27T06:00:00-00:44"
                            >January 27, 1943—6 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. My telegram No. 11, January 26, 10 a.m. The amendments to the bill passed by
                    the Senate yesterday have been telegraphed to Akron with the request to forward
                    them to the Department immediately. They do not alter the bill materially. It
                    will be presented to the House today where amendments will unquestionably be
                    agreed to. Barclay has 5 days in which to sign but present indications are that
                    he will do so at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hibbard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
